issues.shortMessage: Refactor your code not to use hardcoded absolute paths or URIs.
issues.fullMessage: Hardcoding a URI makes it difficult to test a program: path literals are not always portable across operating systems, a given absolute path may not exist on a specific test environment, a specified Internet URL may not be available when executing the tests, production environment filesystems usually differ from the development environment, ...etc. For all those reasons, a URI should never be hardcoded. Instead, it should be replaced by customizable parameter.

properties.title: URIs should not be hardcoded
